"&#xa0;\nOAR008\n                                  \n                                             \n&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by the Association of Colleges (AoC)&#xa0;\nAoC\n represents further education and sixth form colleges in England, incorporated under the Further and Higher Education Act 1992. The 157 Group is a consortium of\n&#xa0;\n30 of the UK’s largest FE colleges. The Group offers a UK-wide view of educational practice and policy development.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;The Social and Economic imperative&#xa0;\n&#xa0;GCSE English and maths achievement&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Preparing young people to progress to employment &#xa0;Careers Guidance&#xa0;\nJanuary 2014\n&#xa0;\n \nSee, for example, the work of Professor Robert Coe of Durham University at \nhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/education-24079951\n Paragraph 21, HMCI Annual Report\n Ibid\n \nAs a result of a \nDfE\n consultation in 2013, vocational qualifications will be classified as ‘occupational’ if they lead to a specific job and ‘applied general’ if they are more generic\n including from the All Party Parliamentary Group on Local Growth at \nhttp://appglocalgrowth.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/appg-skills-inquiry-report_lowres.pdf\n which is why the recommendation for closer relationships between LEPs and Colleges was included in the 2013 Budget documents by the Chancellor of the Exchequer\n"